{
  "text": "Brettanomyces spp. are most commonly associated with spoilage in beer, wine, and soft drink due to the production of many off-flavour metabolites including acetic acid, and vinyl-and ethyl-phenols [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . However, Brettanomyces can also represent an important and favorable component of traditional Belgian Lambic beers [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , and their use has increased in recent years in the craft brewing industry [CITATION_6] . Furthermore, B. bruxellensis has shown potential in bioethanol production by outcompeting S. cerevisiae and for its ability to utilize novel substrates [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
  "correct_citation": {
